'''霜震'''（{{lang-en|'''Frost quake'''}}<ref name="wisconsin">{{cite web|url=http://www.uwm.edu/Dept/Geosciences/qketour/frostqke/cryoseis.html|title=Milwaukee Area Frostquakes|accessdate=2006-10-22|date=1994-02-24|publisher=[[University_of_Wisconsin–Milwaukee|University of Wisconsin–Milwaukee]]|archive-date=2007-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070104124542/http://www.uwm.edu/Dept/Geosciences/qketour/frostqke/cryoseis.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="MGS">{{cite web|url=http://www.maine.gov/doc/nrimc/mgs/explore/hazards/quake/quake-cryoseism.htm|title=Cryoseisms in Maine|accessdate=2006-10-21|date=2005-10-06|publisher=Maine Geological Survey, [[Maine|the State of Maine]]|archive-date=2013-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130507082901/http://www.maine.gov/doc/nrimc/mgs/explore/hazards/quake/quake-cryoseism.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，學名{{lang|en|'''Cryoseism'''}}），亦作'''冰震'''、'''凍結地震'''或'''地震霜'''<ref>{{cite episode |url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l1Td2_iUAYI |date=2014-01-04 |accessdate=2014-01-06 |title=加拿大人最近體驗到的較新自然現像 Frost Quake*，火星一號計劃首次運送地球人移居火星*，聽眾分享拉斯維加斯酒店靈異經歷* |series=[[星空奇談|星空奇談]] |language=zh |archive-date=2016-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161006150015/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l1Td2_iUAYI |dead-url=no }}</ref>，是一種在氣溫急劇下降下所出現的自然現象，起因於被水分[[飽和|飽和]]的泥土或岩石<ref name="shortnote">{{cite web|url=http://www.uwm.edu/Dept/Geosciences/qketour/frostqke/lacroix.html|title=A Short Note on Cryoseisms|accessdate=2006-10-21|author=Andrew V. Lacroix|work=Earthquake Notes|date=January 1980|archive-date=2007-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070104124323/http://www.uwm.edu/Dept/Geosciences/qketour/frostqke/lacroix.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。由於當中的水分被快速冷凍至[[冰點|冰點]]時膨脹，對周邊環境產生[[應力|應力]]，從而把泥土或岩石撐開引起衝擊波<ref name="wnb">{{cite web|url=http://weathernotebook.org/transcripts/2000/04/14.html|title=Cryoseisms Explained|accessdate=2006-10-21|author=Dave Thurlow|work=The Weather Notebook|publisher=Mount Washington Observatory|date=2000-04-14|language=en|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051124034552/http://www.weathernotebook.org/transcripts/2000/04/14.html|archivedate=2005-11-24}}</ref>。

原來霜震只發生在[[凍土|凍土]]、[[冰河|冰河]]或[[北極圈|北極圈]]附近一些含大量[[地表水|地表水]]的泥土<ref name="wnb" />，但隨着地球各地的氣候變得極端，就連比較南部的一些大城市，例如[[加拿大|加拿大]]的[[多倫多|多倫多]]及[[南安大略省|南安大略省]]的氣溫從2013年聖誕左右的零下十多度跌至2014年元旦後的零下廿多三十度，亦引發這種自然現象<ref>{{cite news |url=http://rt.com/news/frost-quakes-canada-toronto-230/ |title=Canadians experience jolting 'frost quakes' as temperatures plunge |date=2014-01-06 |accessdate=2014-01-06 |language=en |publisher=[[RT_News|RT News]] |archive-date=2020-12-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204200610/https://www.rt.com/news/frost-quakes-canada-toronto-230/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
霜震令居民聽到類似燒槍或[[音爆|音爆]]的巨響<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/what-is-a-frost-quake-2014-1#ixzz2pef7XdNl |title=It's So Cold In Canada The Ground Has Literally Been Cracking Open |author=Christina Sterbenz |date=2014-01-05 |language=en |publisher=[[Business_Insider|Business Insider]] |accessdate=2014-01-06 |archive-date=2019-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629030918/https://www.businessinsider.com/what-is-a-frost-quake-2014-1#ixzz2pef7XdNl |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

